==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maverick
<hw>Mav"er*ick</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>In the southwestern
part of the united States, a bullock or heifer that has not been
branded, and is unclaimed or wild; -- said to be from
<etsep>Maverick</etsep>, the name of a cattle owner in Texas who
neglected to brand his cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maverick</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Maverick
<hw>Mav"er*ick</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To take a
maverick.</def> <mark>[Western U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maverick brand</ent>⟦br⟧
